@page "/my"
@attribute [Authorize]

@* PROTECTED PAGE. The [Authorize] attribute is the auth wall: an unauthenticated
   visitor is sent to the login page (see AuthorizeRouteView -> RedirectToLogin in
   Routes.razor) and returned here after signing in. Most pages are public by default;
   only pages/actions that need a signed-in user carry [Authorize]. *@

<PageTitle>My Calendar</PageTitle>

<h1>My Calendar</h1>

<AuthorizeView>
    <p>Signed in as <strong>@context.User.Identity?.Name</strong>.</p>
</AuthorizeView>

<p>
    This is your private area. Your availability slots and the bookings where you are the
    attendee will live here (Phase 1). Browsing other people's calendars is public; this
    page requires you to be signed in.
</p>
